.TH "vmw_dumb_create" 9 "vmw_dumb_create" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vmw_dumb_create \- Create a dumb kms buffer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" vmw_dumb_create
.BI "(struct drm_file *file_priv "  ","
.BI "struct drm_device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct drm_mode_create_dumb *args "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "file_priv" 12
Pointer to a struct drm_file identifying the caller.
.IP "dev" 12
Pointer to the drm device.
.IP "args" 12
Pointer to a struct drm_mode_create_dumb structure
.SH "RETURN"
Zero on success, negative error code on failure.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is a driver callback for the core drm create_dumb functionality.
Note that this is very similar to the vmw_bo_alloc ioctl, except
that the arguments have a different format.
